 governing; and the effects of transnational capitalist exchanges, which convert everything into a cost-benefit analysis, and which make us all complicit in ways we do not fully grasp. Baez and Boyles examine these forces and offer an alternative to the current pushes to make educational inquiry scientific.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aEducation : Education Policy and Leadership. 4aEducation : Educational Research. 4aEducation : Foundations of Education. 4aEducation : Philosophy of Education. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh1 aBoyles, Deron, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147706940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477069423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477069/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles